content: Today's lesson topic is very important - we will make a research for RIF about opening rules.
As you know, in May 2006 RIF will choose a new rule.
and there are now 8 candidates for new opening rule.
Did you all see those 8 candidates?
here is the file, containing the whole process.
the whole discussion about rules has been carried out in Renjuclass Forum
i am surprised that the Students of Renjuclass do not read their own forum.
how many of you really care about future of renju?
i 'am not strong enough to care about future of renju..
in 3 months, renju will have biggest changes in history.
it is possible for every single person, to contribute to this process
there have been 3 big meetings online,
between the representatives of all renju countries.
They decided following - to measure all rules candidates by 7 criteria,

.
- the new rule should not be very different from the current rule (the smaller is the change, the better)
- the new rule should give more playable (balanced) variants than the current rule
- it should be fair to both players (one player should not have too big "home preparation" advantage)
- it should be easy for beginners to learn rules and to play by these rules
- it should include all or nearly all the existing theory
- there should be no strange "far-away" moves be possible during the opening stage
- the first move should be in the center
- the possibility for both players to avoid opponent's "sure-draw" tactics
in fact, now there are 8 criteria. the last one was added recently.
please take a moment to review these. can you understand all 8?
based on first 7 criteria, we evaluated all 31 rules proposals.
and finally, there were 8 rules proposals left.
which will be further discussed in next big meetings.

For those 8 rules, we added the 8th criterion - the possibility for both players to avoid opponent's "sure-draw" tactics
-
the next meeting will be in March 5.
http://renju.compute.com.tw/~renjuclass/cgi-bin/forum/forums.cgi?forum=25 There you can find the complete information.
